# Commit standards

## Never add Cursor co-author trailers

Do **not** include any of the following in commit messages:

- `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
- Any `Co-authored-by` line referencing `cursor.com`, `cursoragent`, or Cursor

Commits must contain only the human-authored message body and subject.

## Before committing

- Review `git log -1 --format=%B` and ensure no Cursor co-author lines are present.
- The repo hook at `.githooks/prepare-commit-msg` strips these lines automatically when `core.hooksPath` is set.

## Amending

If a hook or tool injects a Cursor trailer, remove it before pushing. Never push commits that contain Cursor co-author attribution.
